The Fisherman's Wharf,Shishir,"Fisherman's wharf used to be our fav joint when we lived in Goa. Excellent food and bevs.
Then we moved to Hyderabad, FMW followed.
We were so happy, to have a Goan restaurant just 5 min drive from home.
In the beginning it was great place to dine. Then it started getting local. Fishes started getting stale, fewer varieties ..Not so great.
Now , after about 3 years, it's more a typical curry point.
We ordered Mutton Xacuti and Kingfish Richado.
Fish was so firm and overcooked, richado overloaded with sweetness.
Mutton was out of the world, with heaps of Curry leaves(Kadi patta/Karia paku) , super high on heat....Reminded me of a Rayala curry in Dindi (Godavari distt ). Meat was cooked with extra affection that it took me 5 min to chew it like a bubblegum. I really thank myself for not ordering more.
Fisherman's wharf- such a disappointment.",1.0,3/19/2019 22:30,fisherman s wharf used to be our fav joint when we lived in goa excellent food and bevs then we moved to hyderabad fmw followed we were so happy to have a goan restaurant just min drive from home in the beginning it was great place to dine then it started getting local fishes started getting stale fewer varieties not so great now after about years it s more a typical curry point we ordered mutton xacuti and kingfish richado fish was so firm and overcooked richado overloaded with sweetness mutton was out of the world with heaps of curry leaves kadi patta karia paku super high on heat reminded me of a rayala curry in dindi godavari distt meat was cooked with extra affection that it took me min to chew it like a bubblegum i really thank myself for not ordering more fisherman s wharf such a disappointment,852,1,150
